auto-detect-algorithm.help: Auto detection algorithms used in tunnel negotiations.
auto-detect-algorithm.name: auto-detect-algorithm

options.help: Use the same TCP option value in SYN/SYNACK packets. Backward compatible.
options.name: simple

options.help: Use different TCP option values in SYN/SYNACK packets to avoid false positive detection.
options.name: diff-req-resp

host-id.help: Local host ID (must also be entered in the remote FortiGate's peer list).
host-id.name: host-id

tunnel-ssl-algorithm.help: Relative strength of encryption algorithms accepted during tunnel negotiation.
tunnel-ssl-algorithm.name: tunnel-ssl-algorithm

options.help: High encryption. Allow only AES and ChaCha.
options.name: high

options.help: Medium encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, and RC4.
options.name: medium

options.help: Low encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, RC4, and DES.
options.name: low
